Information for the Football Game Tonight:

Please be aware that UIL has strict regulations that we must follow.

Everyone must wear a mask if you are 10 years or older.

Be sure to maintain social distance when sitting in the bleachers. We have restricted the amount of tickets by 50% so there is room for distancing.

We are required to screen you as you come in the gate to know if you have COVID symptoms or if you have been exposed to someone that has tested positive for COVID.

Thanks for your help in this matter so we can continue having games and cheering on our Tigers!

post_text:
A few important things:

* The doors will not open until 7:30 am each day. Students do NOT need to be dropped off before this time. Tardy bell rings at 7:48 am. School will release at 3:40 pm.

* Every student needs a water bottle that can be closed. No cups. Must be a water bottle. The water fountains will not be available for use but water bottles can be filled.

*Dress code will be enforced. It’s been a long time since you have had to think about dress code! Make sure your hair cut, color, clothes, etc are all in code!

We will begin school on August 12th in person. We will also offer remote instruction. Please see detailed information in the link.

Please note: The remote instruction will look DRASTICALLY different than last spring. It will be all online. It will require the student to be in attendance (online) during the entire school day with the same rigor of instruction and assignments.

We will have a survey that parents need to fill out for each student to let us know which form of instruction you choose. You will need to commit for a grading period (9 weeks). We will get this out by the end of the week.

post_text:
Hey students! I have heard there might be a rumor going around among you that you don’t have to do the work during this time and we will still pass you to the next grade. This is NOT true! We are grading every paper that comes in and documenting who is turning it in and who isn’t. This time is still important! We are not on a break.....we are just learning from home! Please be sure you are doing your work to the best of your ability! If you have any questions, email your teacher so they can help. They want to help! They miss you! Remember, you will need the information you learn this year for next year!

Miss you guys! ~Mrs. Sanders

shared_text:
Hank the Cowdog
April 8 at 6:50 AM ·

Howdy, Hank Readers! For the next 4 DAYS, the ebook version of "Ranching and Livestock" is FREE!!
We hope it brightens your week!! AND, there is a FREE curriculum to accompany it, with fun activities and work-sheets, so that you can become an expert in ranching! (http://www.depts.ttu.edu/nrhc/Learn/ranchlife.php)

About the book (which is narrated by Hank): "The National Ranching Heritage Center is proud to partner with Hank the Cowdog for the Ranch Life Learning series. In this first book, Ranching and Livestock, the same cast of characters you’ve come to know and love in the Hank the Cowdog series will give you a first-class introduction to ranching! You’ll learn things like: the difference between a ranch and a farm, how cows digest grass, what it takes to run a ranch as a successful business, how to take care of cattle through the various seasons, and much more!"

https://www.amazon.com/Ranching-Livestock-Book-Ranch-Learning-ebook/dp/B086J7P12Y/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=%22ranching+and+livestock%22&qid=1586219397&sr=8-1

TEA message April 6

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

post_text:
Students and Parents--Yearbook staff needs your help!!

Because of our current situation and not knowing when we will return to school, we would like to have pictures of our students doing school work, art projects, science experiments, outdoor activities, etc. So, please take some pictures then SHARE THEM WITH US.

Download the ReplayIt app by Josten's. Register for an account, then upload those photos. Please tag the photos based on what the activity is, but don't use student names. Images will be filtered to make sure they are appropriate and everything uploaded will be visible to those with the app.

Thanks in advance for sharing! This may be what we have to use to fill our yearbook. 😢

post_text:
While we are out this week, each teacher has posted their assignments on their website. Please visit each of your teachers' websites to find out what they have for you. You will turn this in when you come back to school.

Go to www.oglesbyisd.net. Choose your campus (Elementary PK-5 and Secondary 6 - 12) under the campus tab and then click "View Website" under the teacher's name.

As of right now, we are expected to return on March 23rd. We will continue to monitor the situation and update you as decisions are made.

*Dual Credit Students (English 1302) - Finish your research paper that is due this week. Keep checking Facebook for the latest information.

*Students with online classes - Please log on during the hours of 8:00 am to 3:00 pm to work on those classes.

It has just been released that the Governor has waived all STAAR tests for this year. There are many questions that go along with this that we do not have answers to. As we receive information, we will share it with you.

Enjoy your time with your kids!

These three members have spent the last couple of months diligently learning numerous facts about Agriculture, FFA, and Parliamentary Procedures. They finished sixth in the Nazareth Junior Quiz last Friday and took seventh today in the Bosque River District LDEs. (Very close contest) Kyra Escamilla was fourth place High Point on Friday.

Eighth grader, Addison Hamilton, also spoke all five paragraphs of The FFA Creed. She has come very far in working on her public speaking skills. She finished eighth place in the Greenhand division today.

It is with a very heavy heart that we let you know that we lost one of the greatest men that has been a part of Oglesby ISD on Friday night.

Services for Travis Melvin “Butch” Goodwin have been set. Visitation will be on Tuesday evening from 6-8 at Oakcrest Funeral Home on Bosque in Waco. The funeral will also be held at Oakcrest on Wednesday at 10 am. Internment will be at Eagle Springs following the funeral.

post_text:
PreK and Kindergarten Round Up will be this Wednesday, April 4th in the library from 6:00 pm-7:00 pm.

This registration will be for PreK and K students that will be entering school for the first time in the fall of 2018.

PreK children must be four years old on or before September 1, 2018 and kindergarten children must be five years old on or before September 1, 2018.

Parents will need to bring the following items to Round Up:
Copy of child’s birth certificate
Current shot records
Child’s social security card
Proof of residence (water bill or electric bill)
Two emergency contact phone numbers for the child
Driver’s license of parent/guardian

post_text:
The Lady Tiger Basketball team has advanced to the first round of playoffs. They will play Aquilla on Tuesday, February 13th in McGregor. Game time is 6:00 pm. Admission is $5 per adult and $2 per student.

The Lady Tigers will play a warm-up game this Friday against Blum at home. The game will start at 5:00 pm, just prior to the boys game against Bartlett.
